Description: Papyrus (five fragments, four very small); Demotic text recto. The larger fragment, no. 2, has eight lines of text. Torn at top and on both sides, but lower margin preserved. Previously mounted with EA 10514.
Curator's comments: The larger fragment is part of a land lease.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (327) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/327)
